cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing tasks such as part-of-speech tagging and morphological tagging. The use of recurrent neural networks and meta-models also suggests a focus on machine learning techniques for language processing, which is a common theme in cs.CL.

The paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) because of the use of machine learning models and techniques, including recurrent neural networks and meta-models. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category because the paper deals with the development of models that can learn to combine different types of information for improved performance on language processing tasks.

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category because of the focus on recurrent neural networks and their use in the models presented in the paper.

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible because of the use of neural networks and the focus on developing models that can effectively encode and process contextual information.
